            "text": "<summary>Show English translation</summary>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Let's wake up!",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "</details>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "It was signed by Mathilde Brasilier, Inès Chatin, and Blandine de Chalon. On the page they describe themselves as three women who suffered childhood sexual abuse at the hands of influential men in the Saint-Germain-des-Prés milieu. They argue that a closed ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "entre-soi",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " - the same tight habit of mutual protection among the powerful - still muffles complaints and shields impunity for child sexual crime. They call for that silence to break in the open: they name the milieu they say hid the harm and put the question in daylight - who was protected, and who still moves as if nothing on the page had changed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Les hommes de la rue du Bac in Libération",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Libération",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " set out the file in named, checkable pieces rather than rumor: first by identifying Inès Chatin and locating the alleged network in Paris (7th arrondissement, rue du Bac / Saint-Germain-des-Prés), then by tracking specific institutional follow-up where it is documented in the sources.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "As coverage deepened, each publication added another layer to the same story.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "On 11 July 2025 ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Libération",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " dated the story under this French headline:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "« François Gibault relaxé par l'ordre des avocats après les révélations d'Inès Chatin sur des violences sexuelles »",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<details class=\"translate\">",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<summary>Show English translation</summary>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "François Gibault cleared by the Paris Bar after Inès Chatin's revelations about sexual violence.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "</details>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "That reporting line was about professional discipline, not a criminal verdict. After an inquiry opened following the newspaper's ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Les hommes de la rue du Bac",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " investigation series, the Paris Bar's governing body, the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Ordre des avocats",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " du barreau de Paris, cleared Gibault in that forum: no bar sanction. Other coverage records that he denied the allegations to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Libération",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Libération kept publishing dated reporting on the file across the months that followed; the next fixed dates on the public calendar are in April 2026, when broadcast interviews widened the story again.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Le Grand portrait, 7 April 2026",
