      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "In that broadcast, Chatin speaks about adoption, about a couple she experienced as a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "façade",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", and about the name ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "“Gaston”",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " - her adoptive father's original first name - which she uses because she refuses to grant him the role of a father. The exchange leads into this studio line, with English in the fold below.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "« Je lui dénie la possibilité d'avoir été un père »",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<details class=\"translate\">",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
