            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "That piece traced the aftermath of the first shock wave. France Info (public news radio) and France 3 Régions (regional public television) carried the map into Charente-Maritime (Atlantic-western France): on-the-record testimony, and archival material on how prefects and departmental public-health directors had once challenged how a nursery in Bourcefranc-le-Chapus was run.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The same sources tie that childcare setting to Chatin's adoption dossier and to trafficking-related lines of inquiry into how children were counted, registered, and moved between services. Prefect and public-health memoranda are how those outlets document institutional unease - staffing, registers, who passed through the doors - not a substitute for criminal findings on every allegation now in circulation. Later versions of the same Libération reporting sometimes carried corrections or addenda when editors revised the story.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "She also describes violence in the home and a silence so heavy that, in her telling, bruises could be seen and still the door stayed closed. Those sentences cost something to say out loud. In broadcast she holds them in ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "her",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " pacing and ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "her",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " voice - not splintered into social clips stripped of context.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "In that busy stretch of early April 2026, Chatin was on the record about the rue du Bac circle, the cost of silence in wealthy households, and the pressure on victims not to name abusers. The same week, ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "France Info",
            "marks": [
              "em"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " published an online piece drawing on her first long national-radio interview of the month, also recording her insistence that families stop shielding perpetrators. It quoted two lines in French:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "« J'aimerais qu'on arrive à dire les noms tout haut, pour mieux protéger les victimes »",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<details class=\"translate\">",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<summary>Show English translation</summary>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I would like us to be able to say the names out loud, to better protect victims.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "</details>",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "« que les familles arrêtent de protéger les agresseurs »",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "<details class=\"translate\">",
